gpGenericResolveProtocol.description: Default host protocol to use when starting a dedicated port and the protocol is not explicitly specified in the command. Is set to one of 'telnet', connect, or any. Any means to try LAT (connect) first and if that fails, try telnet. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'resolve-protocol. Note: This object is not valid for Synchronous ports.

gpSignalInputStartChar.name: gpSignalInputStartChar
gpSignalInputStartChar.description: The control character sequence that restarts input if the charPortInFlowType parameter (in the char MIB) is set to xonXoff. This value of this object can be either a single displayable character or two characters of the form '^x', where '^x' is translated as 'Control-x'. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'input-start-char'. Note: This object is not valid for synchronous ports.

gpSignalInputStopChar.name: gpSignalInputStopChar
gpSignalInputStopChar.description: The control character sequence that stops input if the charPortInFlowType parameter (in the char MIB) is set to xonXoff. This value of this object can be either a single displayable character or two characters of the form '^x', where '^x' is translated as 'Control-x'. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'input-stop-char'. Note: This object is not valid for synchronous ports.

gpSignalOutputStartChar.name: gpSignalOutputStartChar
gpSignalOutputStartChar.description: The control character sequence that restarts output if the charPortOutFlowType parameter (in the char MIB) is set to xonXoff. This value of this object can be either a single displayable character or two characters of the form '^x', where '^x' is translated as 'Control-x'. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'output-start-char'. Note: This object is not valid for synchronous ports.

gpSignalOutputStopChar.name: gpSignalOutputStopChar
gpSignalOutputStopChar.description: The control character sequence that stops output if the charPortOutFlowType parameter (in the char MIB) is set to xonXoff. This value of this object can be either a single displayable character or two characters of the form '^x', where '^x' is translated as 'Control-x'. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'output-stop-char'. Note: This object is not valid for synchronous ports.

gpSignalIxanyFlowCtrl.name: gpSignalIxanyFlowCtrl
gpSignalIxanyFlowCtrl.description: This parameter specifies whether any input character will be treated as a start (xon) character when output has been suspended by a stop (xoff) character. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'ixany-flow-control'. Note: This object is not valid for synchronous ports.

gpSignalForwardKey.name: gpSignalForwardKey
gpSignalForwardKey.description: Defines a control character sequence as an attention character to switch the user to the next session. The Annex-II only allows a single control character (eg. ^A), while the Annex3 and MicroAnnex allow a string of control characters to be defined (eg. ^A^B^Z). This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'forward-key'. Note: This object is not valid for synchronous ports.

gpSignalBackwardKey.name: gpSignalBackwardKey
gpSignalBackwardKey.description: Defines a control character sequence as an attention character to switch the user to the previous session. The Annex-II only allows a single control character (eg. ^A), while the Annex3 and MicroAnnex allow a string of control characters to be defined (eg. ^A^B^Z). This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'Backward-key'. Note: This object is not valid for Synchronous ports.

gpLoginVciLoginPortPasswd.name: gpLoginVciLoginPortPasswd
gpLoginVciLoginPortPasswd.description: Enables the port password if the port is configured as a DECServer interface port. The default is disabled. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'login-port-password'.

gpLoginVciLoginTimeout.name: gpLoginVciLoginTimeout
gpLoginVciLoginTimeout.description: Enables a login timer if the port is configured as a DECServer interface port. The default is disabled. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'login-timeout'.

gpTimerForwardTimer.name: gpTimerForwardTimer
gpTimerForwardTimer.description: This parameter defines the inter-character timer that sets the amount of time, in tens of milliseconds, that will elapse before forwarding the received data. The value of 5 turns off the timer. Setting this object to 0 causes the default value of 5 to be used. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'forwarding-timer'.

gpTimerForwardCount.name: gpTimerForwardCount
gpTimerForwardCount.description: Specifies the number of received characters buffered for the port by the Annex before forwarding the characters to the host or network. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'forwarding-count'.

gpTimerCliInactivity.name: gpTimerCliInactivity
gpTimerCliInactivity.description: The amount of time, in minutes, that the Annex waits before hanging up the serial/ta port after it becomes idle. A value of 0 turns off the timer. A value of 255 means immediate, which causes the Annex to hang up the port immediately after exiting from the last job. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'cli-inactivity'.

gpTimerInactivityTimer.name: gpTimerInactivityTimer
gpTimerInactivityTimer.description: The amount of time, in minutes, which a port can remain inactive before the Annex terminates all sessions and resets the port. A value of 0 disables the timer. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'inactivity-timer'.

gpTimerInputIsActivity.name: gpTimerInputIsActivity
gpTimerInputIsActivity.description: Controls whether received input characters are considered as activity for the port. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'input-is-activity'.

gpTimerOutputIsActivity.name: gpTimerOutputIsActivity
gpTimerOutputIsActivity.description: Controls whether transmitted output characters are considered as activity for the port. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'output-is-activity'.

gpTimerResetIdleTimer.name: gpTimerResetIdleTimer
gpTimerResetIdleTimer.description: Defines whether input or output resets the idle timer for the port. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'reset-idle-time-on'.

gpTimerLongBreak.name: gpTimerLongBreak
gpTimerLongBreak.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex returns the user to the CLI prompt after receiving a break greater than two seconds. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'long-break'.

gpTimerShortBreak.name: gpTimerShortBreak
gpTimerShortBreak.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex returns the user to the CLI prompt after receiving a break shorter than two seconds. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'short-break'.

gpSecurityUserName.name: gpSecurityUserName
gpSecurityUserName.description: A string defining the default user name for the user of this serial/ta port. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta/sync port parameter 'user-name'.

gpSecurityCli.name: gpSecurityCli
gpSecurityCli.description: This parameter controls whether security is enabled for the port. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'cli-security'.

gpSecurityConnect.name: gpSecurityConnect
gpSecurityConnect.description: This parameter controls whether the host-based security policy is enabled for access from the port to the network. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'connect-security'.

gpSecurityPortServer.name: gpSecurityPortServer
gpSecurityPortServer.description: This parameter controls whether the host-based security policy is enabled for access to the port from the port server. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'port-server-security'.

gpSecurityPortPasswd.name: gpSecurityPortPasswd
gpSecurityPortPasswd.description: This parameter defines a password for the port for local password protection. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta/sync port parameter 'port-password'.

gpSecurityIpsoClass.name: gpSecurityIpsoClass
gpSecurityIpsoClass.description: Defines the IP security classification for packets sent and received on this port. The default value is none. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'ipso-class'.

gpSecurityIpx.name: gpSecurityIpx
gpSecurityIpx.description: Controls whether IPX security is enabled on this port. The default is disabled. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'ipx-security'.

gpLineEditAttnChar.name: gpLineEditAttnChar
gpLineEditAttnChar.description: Defines a control character sequence as an attention character to return the user to the CLI prompt. The Annex-II only allows x a single control character (eg. ^A), while the Annex3 and MicroAnnex allow a string of control characters to be defined (eg. ^A^B^Z). This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'attn-string'.

gpLineEditEcho.name: gpLineEditEcho
gpLineEditEcho.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex echoes all characters as they are received from the port. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'echo'.

gpLineEditTelnetEscape.name: gpLineEditTelnetEscape
gpLineEditTelnetEscape.description: Defines the control character that returns the user to the 'telnet:' prompt when running the CLI telnet command. This value of this object can be either a single displayable character or two characters of the form '^x', where '^x' is translated as 'Control-x'. The value 'U' disables this feature on the specified port. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'telnet-escape'.

gpLineEditTelnetCRLF.name: gpLineEditTelnetCRLF
gpLineEditTelnetCRLF.description: Defines what characters are transmitted out the port to the network when the End-of-Line character is sensed. 'enabled' means transmit Line-Feed and Carriage-Return. 'disabled' means transmit Carriage-Return and NULL. The default is enabled. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'telnet-crlf'.

gpLineEditMapToLower.name: gpLineEditMapToLower
gpLineEditMapToLower.description: When enabled, the Annex translates all upper case characters to lower case as they are received from the port. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'map-to-lower'.

gpLineEditMapToUpper.name: gpLineEditMapToUpper
gpLineEditMapToUpper.description: When enabled, the Annex translates all lower case characters to upper case as they are transmitted to the port. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'map-to-upper'.

gpLineEditCharErase.name: gpLineEditCharErase
gpLineEditCharErase.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex echoes the character erase and word erase characters for a video terminal (enabled) or for a hard-copy terminal (disabled). This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'char-erase'.

gpLineEditEraseChar.name: gpLineEditEraseChar
gpLineEditEraseChar.description: Defines the character erase control character sequence. This value of this object can be either a single displayable character or two characters of the form '^x', where '^x' is translated as 'Control-x'. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'erase-char'.

gpLineEditLineErase.name: gpLineEditLineErase
gpLineEditLineErase.description: This parameter controls whether the Annex echoes the line erase character for a video terminal (enabled) or for a hard-copy terminal (disabled). This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'line-erase'.

gpLineEditEraseLine.name: gpLineEditEraseLine
gpLineEditEraseLine.description: Defines the line erase control character sequence. This value of this object can be either a single displayable character or two characters of the form '^x', where '^x' is translated as 'Control-x'. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'erase-line'.

gpLineEditEraseWord.name: gpLineEditEraseWord
gpLineEditEraseWord.description: Defines the word erase control character sequence. This value of this object can be either a single displayable character or two characters of the form '^x', where '^x' is translated as 'Control-x'. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'erase-word'.

gpLineEditHardwareTabs.name: gpLineEditHardwareTabs
gpLineEditHardwareTabs.description: When enabled, this parameter allows the Annex to expand ASCII tab characters. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'hardware-tabs'.

gpLineEditRedisplayLine.name: gpLineEditRedisplayLine
gpLineEditRedisplayLine.description: Defines the reprint line control character sequence. This value of this object can be either a single displayable character or two characters of the form '^x', where '^x' is translated as 'Control-x'. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'redisplay-line'.

gpLineEditToggleOutput.name: gpLineEditToggleOutput
gpLineEditToggleOutput.description: Defines the flush control character used to flush the output buffer. This value of this object can be either a single displayable character or two characters of the form '^x', where '^x' is translated as 'Control-x'. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'toggle-output'.

gpLineEditNewLineTerm.name: gpLineEditNewLineTerm
gpLineEditNewLineTerm.description: This parameter controls whether a carriage return is echoed as just a carriage return (enabled), or whether the carriage return is echoed as a carriage return and line feed. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'newline-terminal'.

gpNetLocalAddr.name: gpNetLocalAddr
gpNetLocalAddr.description: The Internet address for the Annex's side of the point-to-point (SLIP or PPP) link. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous, ta, synchronous port parameter 'local-address'.

gpNetRemoteAddr.name: gpNetRemoteAddr
gpNetRemoteAddr.description: The Internet address for the host at the remote end of the point-to-point (SLIP or PPP) link. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous, ta, synchronous port parameter 'remote-address'.

gpNetPppDialupAddr.name: gpNetPppDialupAddr
gpNetPppDialupAddr.description: local(1) - The annex will get the PPP dialup addresses from the port parameters local-address and remote-address. acp(2) - The Annex requests the PPP dialup addresses from the host-based ACP. dhcp(3) - The Annex requests the PPP dialup addresses from the host-based DHCP. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous, ta, synchronous global port parameter 'address-origin'.

gpNetMetric.name: gpNetMetric
gpNetMetric.description: This parameter defines the hop count to the remote end of the SLIP or PPP interface. Setting this object to 0 defaults to a value of 1. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous, ta. synchronous port parameter 'metric'.

gpNetSlipSecure.name: gpNetSlipSecure
gpNetSlipSecure.description: If anxEnableSecurity is not set, this parameter selects slip session logging. If anxEnableSecurity is set, this parameter permits slip access only from secure ports. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous, ta and sync port parameter 'slip-ppp-security'.

gpNetInactivity.name: gpNetInactivity
gpNetInactivity.description: The number of units allowed for serial protocol inactivity on the port. The type of unit, minutes or seconds, is defined by the object anxpNetInactivityUnits. If the type of units is 'seconds', the actual granularity is only 5 seconds. When the interval expires, the port is automatically reset. A value of 0 disables the timer. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous, ta, synchronous port parameter 'net-inactivity'.

gpNetDoCompression.name: gpNetDoCompression
gpNetDoCompression.description: When enabled, the Annex will attempt to negotiate TCP/IP header compression on this serial link. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta/sync port parameter 'do-compression'.

gpNetAllowCompression.name: gpNetAllowCompression
gpNetAllowCompression.description: When enabled, the Annex will allow TCP/IP header compression on this serial link only if the other end of the serial link initiates the compression. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous, ta, synchronous port parameter 'allow-compression'.

gpNetInactivityUnits.name: gpNetInactivityUnits
gpNetInactivityUnits.description: The type of units that are used for the port's net inactivity timer. See also the anxpNetInactivity object. The default value is 'minutes'. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous, ta, synchronous port parameter 'net-inactivity-units'.

gpSlipSubnetMask.name: gpSlipSubnetMask
gpSlipSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask for this SLIP interface. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta/sync port parameter 'subnet-mask'.

gpSlipMtuSize.name: gpSlipMtuSize
gpSlipMtuSize.description: Force the compressed SLIP interface to use a Maximum Transmission Unit (MTU) of either 1024 bytes (large) or 256 bytes (small). The default is large. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta/sync port parameter 'slip-mtu-size'.

gpSlipNoIcmp.name: gpSlipNoIcmp
gpSlipNoIcmp.description: When enabled, the Annex will discard any ICMP packets directed to this SLIP link. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta/sync port parameter 'slip-no-icmp'.

gpSlipTos.name: gpSlipTos
gpSlipTos.description: When enabled, the Annex sends interactive traffic over this SLIP link before any other traffic. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta/sync port parameter 'slip-tos'.

gpPPPMru.name: gpPPPMru
gpPPPMru.description: This parameter defines the maximum receive unit in bytes. The default value is 1500. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous, ta, and synchronous port parameter 'ppp-mru'.

gpPPPAcm.name: gpPPPAcm
gpPPPAcm.description: This parameter specifies which of the first 32 bytes (0x00, ... 0x1F) can be sent as clear text and which need to be escaped. A bit on in the mask indicates the character must be escaped. The mask should be specified as an 8 hex character string (0x1F000000 and 1F000000 are both acceptable). This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta/sync port parameter 'ppp-acm'.

gpPPPSecurityProto.name: gpPPPSecurityProto
gpPPPSecurityProto.description: Defines which security protocol will be used to authenticate the remote user. This parameter must be set and the Annex enable-security (anxEnableSecurity) must be enabled before authentication is performed. The default is none This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta/sync port parameter 'ppp-security-protocol'.

gpPPPRemoteUser.name: gpPPPRemoteUser
gpPPPRemoteUser.description: The username used by the Annex to identify itself if the remote PPP peer asks for authentication. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta/sync port parameter 'ppp-username-remote'.

gpPPPRemotePasswd.name: gpPPPRemotePasswd
gpPPPRemotePasswd.description: The password used by the Annex to identify itself if the remote PPP peer asks for authentication. Reading this parameter will return either <set> if the password is defined or <unset> if the password is not defined. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta/sync port parameter 'ppp-password-remote'.

gpPPPNcp.name: gpPPPNcp
gpPPPNcp.description: A bitmask to set the PPP NCP Options: 0x0001 NCP-ALL 0x0002 NCP-IPCP 0x0004 NCP-ATCP 0x0008 NCP-IPXCP 0x0010 NCP-MP 0x0020 NCP-CCP 0x0040 NCP-CBCP

gpPPPIpxNetwork.name: gpPPPIpxNetwork
gpPPPIpxNetwork.description: The IPX network number for an IPX PPP connection using this port. When the IPX PPP connection is established the network number will be negotiated. If one end of the connection is set to zero then the value from the other end of the connection will be used. The value of this object is an 8 digit hexadecimal number string representing the IPX network segment assigned to this port. The value must be unique across the network domain. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta/sync port parameter 'ppp-ipx-network'.

gpPPPIpxNode.name: gpPPPIpxNode
gpPPPIpxNode.description: The IPX node number for an IPX PPP connection using this port. The value of this object is a 12 digit hexadecimal number string representing the IPX node number assigned to this port. Note the string is expected in the form: 12-3a-4-7-89-23.Each part of the address must be a hex value separated by a hyphen. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta/sync port parameter 'ppp-ipx-node'.

gpARAPGuest.name: gpARAPGuest
gpARAPGuest.description: If enabled, allows ARAP guest login service. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'at-guest'.

gpARAPNodeid.name: gpARAPNodeid
gpARAPNodeid.description: The default AppleTalk node ID hint that is used by the Annex on this port. The address consists of two parts separated by a dot. The address may be in either hex or decimal format. The first part is the network address and ranges from 0 to 65534 (0x0000 to 0xFFFE). The second part is the node address and ranges from 0 to 254 (0x00 to 0xFE). Example: 0x00BF.0xFD 191.253 0x00BF.253 191.0xFD are all the same address. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'at-nodeid'.

gpARAPSecurity.name: gpARAPSecurity
gpARAPSecurity.description: Controls whether ACP service is enabled for this port when establishing an AppleTalk connection. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'at-security'.

gpARAPV42BIS.name: gpARAPV42BIS
gpARAPV42BIS.description: Controls whether V.42bis compression is done during an ARAP session. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'arap-v42bis'.

gpTN3270PrinterHost.name: gpTN3270PrinterHost
gpTN3270PrinterHost.description: The IP address of the machine running a Berkeley-style lpd server. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'tn3270-printer-name'.

gpTN3270PrinterName.name: gpTN3270PrinterName
gpTN3270PrinterName.description: A valid printer name contained in the /etc/printcap file on the remote host. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'tn3270-printer-name'.

gpLATAuthMap.name: gpLATAuthMap
gpLATAuthMap.description: This port parameter is functionally identical to anxpLatAuthGroupVal and corresponds to the NA/admin Annex parameter 'group-value'. The syntax of this object is an octet string 32 bytes long, with the first byte representing groups 0 through 7 and the last byte representing groups 248 through 255. For example, 0x40 0x25 ... means the groups 1,10,13,15 are valid for this port. A returned value with all bits set to zero is the same as setting 'group-value' to 'none'. The object always returns a string 32 bytes long. Note: You may use either this object or anxpLatAuthVal object to read or set the 'group-value' parameter.anxpLatAuthMap is preferred.

gpLATbEnable.name: gpLATbEnable
gpLATbEnable.description: Controls interpretation of LAT Data-B packets received from host. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous/ta port parameter 'latb-enable'.

gpLATMultiSession.name: gpLATMultiSession
gpLATMultiSession.description: This parameter allows multisession operation to be managed on a per port basis. If multisessions for the server has not been enabled, any attempt to use this command will cause the error message 'ETSMIN-786-Multisession feature Disabled' to be displayed. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin port parameter 'multisessions'. Note: * SNMP will not check for the Annex MultiSession parameter. * Setting this MIB object is equivalent to defining the port parameter 'multisession' through NA/admin.

gpcharPortInFlowType.name: gpcharPortInFlowType
gpcharPortInFlowType.description: The port's type of input flow control. 'none' indicates no flow control at this level or below. 'xonXoff' indicates software flow control by recognizing XON and XOFF characters. 'hardware' indicates flow control delegated to the lower level, for example a parallel port. 'ctsRts' and 'dsrDtr' are specific to RS-232-like ports. Although not architecturally pure, they are included here for simplicity's sake. Default is eia or hardware(3).

gpcharPortOutFlowType.name: gpcharPortOutFlowType
gpcharPortOutFlowType.description: The port's type of output flow control. 'none' indicates no flow control at this level or below. 'xonXoff' indicates software flow control by recognizing XON and XOFF characters. 'hardware' indicates flow control delegated to the lower level, for example a parallel port. 'ctsRts' and 'dsrDtr' are specific to RS-232-like ports. Although not architecturally pure, they are included here for simplicy's sake. Default is eia or hardware(3).

gpcharPortSessionMaximum.name: gpcharPortSessionMaximum
gpcharPortSessionMaximum.description: The maximum number of concurrent sessions allowed on the port. A value of -1 indicates no maximum. Setting the maximum to less than the current number of sessions has unspecified results. Default is 3. This MIB object corresponds to NA/Admin parameter 'max-session-count'.

gprs232AsyncPortBits.name: gprs232AsyncPortBits
gprs232AsyncPortBits.description: The port's number of bits in a character. This object corresponds to the admin parameter data-bits

gprs232AsyncPortStopBits.name: gprs232AsyncPortStopBits
gprs232AsyncPortStopBits.description: The port's number of stop bits. This object corresponds to the admin parameter stop-bits

gprs232AsyncPortParity.name: gprs232AsyncPortParity
gprs232AsyncPortParity.description: The port's sense of a character parity bit.

gpV120Mru.name: gpV120Mru
gpV120Mru.description: This parameter defines the maximum receive unit in bytes. The default value is 256. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous, ta, and synchronous port parameter 'v120-mru'.

gpMpMrru.name: gpMpMrru
gpMpMrru.description: This parameter sets the upper limit of the MRRU LCP negotiation. All LCP negotiations will start with this value; negotiation downward only is allowed. The default value is 1500. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous, ta, and synchronous port parameter `mp-mrru'.

gpMpEndPointClass.name: gpMpEndPointClass
gpMpEndPointClass.description: This parameter sets the preference for the Endpoint Discriminator. PPP Magic Number Block(5) isexcluded; it doesn't guarantee unique link identities and could lead to illegal bundle memebership. The default is unitmacaddr(4). This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous, ta, and synchronous port parameter `mp-endpoint-option'.

gpMpEndPointValue.name: gpMpEndPointValue
gpMpEndPointValue.description: This parameter sets the value of the Endpoint Discriminator for options that require user-configured information. This parameter is only valid when gpMPEndPointClass is set to Public Switched Network Directory Number E.164 (6). This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin asynchronous, ta, and synchronous port parameter `mp-endpoint-address'.

gpProxyArpEnable.name: gpProxyArpEnable
gpProxyArpEnable.description: Specifies whether the Annex will proxy ARP all remote IP connections. A value of enabled(1) will allow the Annex to proxy all remote IP connections. A value of disabled(2) allows the Annex to proxy only remote IP connections having the same subnet address as the Annex. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin global port parameter 'proxy-arp-enabled'.

gpPPPTraceLevel.name: gpPPPTraceLevel
gpPPPTraceLevel.description: Controls whether PPP trace messages are sent to the syslog facility or not. The default value is none(0). This MIB object corresponds to the na/admin port parameter ppp-trace-level.

anxTunnelLineIndex.name: anxTunnelLineIndex
anxTunnelLineIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the DS1 interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex from the Interfaces table of MIB-II (RFC 1213). This is unused for the ra2000, ra4000 platforms but needs to be filled in with a 1. Look at anxt1WanModuleTable for an alternative way of getting the interface number for a physical WAN module

anxTunnelUnitIndex.name: anxTunnelUnitIndex
anxTunnelUnitIndex.description: On a PRI interface, this is a call's B channel number ranging from 1 to anxt1TotChan. On a port interface, this is the port number ranging from 1 to ports.totalports.

anxTunnelWanProtocol.name: anxTunnelWanProtocol
anxTunnelWanProtocol.description: This field describes the protocol used on the WAN interface from the Gateway (or Home Agent) to the customer premise equipment (CPE).

anxTunnelWanAddress.name: anxTunnelWanAddress
anxTunnelWanAddress.description: This field describes the WAN Address from the Gateway (or Home Agent) to the customer premise equipment (CPE).

anxTunnelState.name: anxTunnelState
anxTunnelState.description: This fields describes the Tunnel's current state. reserved - visitor added, authentication in progress pending - authentication complete, registration requisition has been sent to gateway, tunnel not registered yet registered - tunnel is up

anxTunnelMnIPAddress.name: anxTunnelMnIPAddress
anxTunnelMnIPAddress.description: The IP Address of the Remote Node.

anxTunnelMnIPXAddress.name: anxTunnelMnIPXAddress
anxTunnelMnIPXAddress.description: The IPX Address of the Remote Node.

anxTunnelHaAddress.name: anxTunnelHaAddress
anxTunnelHaAddress.description: The IP Address assigned to the Home Agent.

ss7Pref1SigGateway.name: ss7Pref1SigGateway
ss7Pref1SigGateway.description: The IP address of the primary SS7 gateway. The default value is 0.0.0.0. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin parameter 'pref1-sig-gateway'.

ss7Pref2SigGateway.name: ss7Pref2SigGateway
ss7Pref2SigGateway.description: The IP address of the primary secondary SS7 gateway. This may be zero if a redundant SS7 gateway is not available. The default value is 0.0.0.0. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin parameter 'pref2-sig-gateway'.

ss7Pref1SigPort.name: ss7Pref1SigPort
ss7Pref1SigPort.description: The TCP port number used on the primary SS7 gateway. The default is 1000. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin parameter 'pref1-sig-port'.

ss7Pref2SigPort.name: ss7Pref2SigPort
ss7Pref2SigPort.description: The TCP port number used on the secondary SS7 gateway. The default is 1000. This entry is zero if no redundant SS7 gateway is available. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin parameter 'pref2-sig-port'.

ss7SigKeepalive.name: ss7SigKeepalive
ss7SigKeepalive.description: The maximum time to wait for a packet to be received from SS7 server. This value is in seconds. The default value is 15 seconds. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin parameter 'sig-keepalive'.

ss7CurrentGateway.name: ss7CurrentGateway
ss7CurrentGateway.description: The address of the current SS7 server. This can change dynamically depending on the state of the server.

ss7ConnectionTime.name: ss7ConnectionTime
ss7ConnectionTime.description: Time at which this connection was established to the current SS7 Gateway.

ss7Registration.name: ss7Registration
ss7Registration.description: Describes whether the RAS can accept and/or receive calls. This is set by the ss7 gateway.

ss7WanIndex.name: ss7WanIndex
ss7WanIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the Wan Module.

ss7ChanNumber.name: ss7ChanNumber
ss7ChanNumber.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the Channel Numnber.

ss7ChanStatus.name: ss7ChanStatus
ss7ChanStatus.description: The status of the ds0 channel. idle(1) - the DS0 is available for calls busy(2) - call is in progress blocked(3) - the RAS of the gateway requested block unblocking(4) - loopback(5) - loopback requested by the gateway restarting(6) - DS0 restart requested by the gateway continuityTest(7) - the RAS or the gateway requested continuity test

ss7ChanState.name: ss7ChanState
ss7ChanState.description: The state of the ds0 channel. idle(1) - no call in progress connected(2) - call fully established. waitReleaseComplete(3) - waiting for Release Complete from gateway. waitATConnect(4) - waiting for connect from WAN manager. waitRelease(5) - waiting for Release from gateway. waitConnect(6) - waiting for connect from gateway.

nfasPref1SigGateway.name: nfasPref1SigGateway
nfasPref1SigGateway.description: The IP address of the primary nfas gateway. The default value is 0.0.0.0. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin parameter 'pref1-sig-gateway'.

nfasPref2SigGateway.name: nfasPref2SigGateway
nfasPref2SigGateway.description: The IP address of the backup nfas gateway. The default value is 0.0.0.0. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin parameter 'pref2-sig-gateway'.

nfasPref1SigPort.name: nfasPref1SigPort
nfasPref1SigPort.description: The TCP port number used on the primary nfas gateway. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin parameter 'pref1-sig-port'.

nfasPref2SigPort.name: nfasPref2SigPort
nfasPref2SigPort.description: The TCP port number used on the nfas backup gateway. This MIB object corresponds to the NA/admin parameter 'pref2-sig-port'.

nfasGroupName.name: nfasGroupName
nfasGroupName.description: This is a trap to indicate the nfas group name.

nfasDchannelstate.name: nfasDchannelstate
nfasDchannelstate.description: This will indicate whether this interface is Active or Inactive : 1-Active, 2-Inactive.

nfasInterfaceStatus.name: nfasInterfaceStatus
nfasInterfaceStatus.description: The type of interface - Primary,Backup or Bearer.

nfasIpAddress.name: nfasIpAddress
nfasIpAddress.description: The IP Address of the Interface.

nfasDchannelStatus.name: nfasDchannelStatus
nfasDchannelStatus.description: The D Channel Status - Active or Inactive.

nfasConnectStatus.name: nfasConnectStatus
nfasConnectStatus.description: The nfas connect status - Connected or Disconnected.

nfasInterfaceNo.name: nfasInterfaceNo
nfasInterfaceNo.description: The nfas interface number which could be beween 0-19. The Interface No for the primary is always 0.

nfasConnectionStatus.name: nfasConnectionStatus
nfasConnectionStatus.description: This is a trap to indicate the nfas connection status between Primary,Backup and Bearer .

nfasBackupStatus.name: nfasBackupStatus
nfasBackupStatus.description: This is a trap to indicate the nfas switch-over status.
